cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the problem of 3D point registration using deep learning techniques. This problem is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) as it involves aligning 3D scans of objects or environments. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that the paper could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) as it deals with the alignment of 3D models.
